
# 365 Truck Customer Application

An application to booking order for rent truck and to buy 
accessary, buy truck . 

Project use [React Native](https://reactnative.dev/) to develop the mobile application.

## Requirement

Node 16 is required. Development for iOS requires a Mac and Xcode 11 or up, and will target iOS 12 and up.

You also need to install the dependencies required by React Native.  
Go to the [React Native environment setup](https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup), then select `React Native CLI Quickstart` tab.  
Follow instructions for your given `development OS` and `target OS`.

## Installation

Clone the project source code to your local device :

```
git clone https://tranvinhan2k@bitbucket.org/fdssoft_com/app_365truck.git
```

Assuming you have all the requirements installed, you can run the project by running:

- `yarn` to download all library packages in soucre code.
- `cd ios & pod install` to download dependencies for IOS project. 
- `yarn start` to start the metro bundler, in a dedicated terminal
- `yarn <platform>` to run the *platform* application (remember to start a simulator or connect a device)


## How to build new APK release version
**Step 1. Delete [index.android.bundle]() in android/app/src/main/assets**

<div align="center">
    <img src="src/assets/images/tutorial/1.png" alt="1-1" width="100%">
</div>

**Step 2. Run in terminal to build new bundle**

```
yarn bundle
```
**Step 3. Run command to release new bundle**

```
yarn release-apk
```

## How to build new TestFlight release version
**Step 1. Open file UserApp.xcworkspace in Mac OS**
```
cd ios & open UserApp.xcworkspace
```
**Step 2. Archive Project**

In Xcode project, Click **Product**, then click **Archive**

![image describe how to open archive](https://i.ytimg.com/vi/39P-KGTpdTs/hqdefault.jpg)

**Step 3. Distribute Application**

After archive process completed, Click **Distribute App**, and click **Next** untill the process is loading

![image describe how to distribute app to project](https://static-assets.codecademy.com/Paths/ios-skill-path/push-your-app-article/Organizer-Distribute-Button.png)

**Step 4. Missing Compliance and submit for reviewing**

Wait for minute and open TestFlight field in [365 Truck User App](https://developer.apple.com/account) and click **Manage** button next to text **Missing Compliance**. 

![image to describe missing comliance step](data:image/png;base64,)

choose **None of the algoralgorithm mentioned above** and click **Next**. If this is new first version, they will review it in 2-3 days.

**Step 5. Add people to project**

Adding people via public link at first menu or send an invitation to people in External Testing Group

![describe public link](https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/5eb4f2c9c01e0c6cc59d6e81/5eccec1fb6d03703cdccada0_Apple-TestFlight-Enable-Confirmation-min.jpeg)

![describe add people in external testing](https://i.stack.imgur.com/MJ4HJ.jpg)
